<SECOND>PM-People-First Lady,0218</SECOND>
<HEAD>Barbara Bush Tosses Out Ball For Son's Baseball Team</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ARLINGTON, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   It was Mother's Day at Arlington Stadium
when first lady Barbara Bush threw out the first pitch for her
son's Texas Rangers before a baseball game against the New York
Yankees.
   Mrs. Bush, surrounded by Secret Service agents and about 35
photographers, emerged from the Rangers dugout to a standing
ovation from the crowd of 26,898 Thursday night. She was
accompanied to the mound by three children enrolled in local
