looked for the sign and laughed.
   Rangers catcher Geno Petralli was standing behind the plate, a
bit too far for the first lady's arm.
   She motioned for him to come out about halfway, then fired a
high fastball that Petralli reached up and grabbed.
   Bush said the toss was his mother's ``first major league
performance. We'll try to get Dad out here next year.''
