<HEAD>Airport Considers $1 Billion Expansion; Asian Tourism Touted</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Spurred by a surge in Asian tourism, San
Francisco International Airport planners are considering a
six-year, $1 billion plan to expand the facility.
   The proposal would include the construction of an international
terminal costing $250 million to $300 million, according to the
airport's preliminary master plan, released Thursday.
   But before the ambitious project can get off the ground, airport
officials will have to contend with critics worried about jet
noise, traffic and air safety.
