<SECOND>AM-BRF--Zimbabwe-Crash,0134</SECOND>
<HEAD>8 Killed When Plane Crashes in Bush</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HARARE, Zimbabwe (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A small plane carrying sugar plantation
executives crashed in southeastern Zimbabwe, killing all eight
people aboard, it was reported Friday.
   State aviation experts were flown to the town of Triangle to
investigate the cause of Thursday night's crash.
   The seven passengers were senior personnel of Triangle Ltd., a
multimillion- dollar company that grows and refines sugar cane, a
company spokesman said.
   They were traveling from the annual Zimbabwe International Trade
Fair in Bulawayo to Buffalo Range airport near Triangle, 200 miles
to the southeast, when the plane crashed, acting managing director
Colin Saunders told the Zimbabwe Inter-African News Agency.
   A search party found the bodies, the managing director said.
Company sources said all aboard were Zimbabweans.
