<HEAD>Helicopter Crash Kills 11</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A helicopter crashed in the port city of Tianjin
on Friday, killing all 11 people aboard, including a Japanese
pilot, the Japanese Embassy said.
   The helicopter, which belonged to the Japanese company Asahi
Koyo, crashed near Tianjin airport, embassy officials said.
   According to the state-run Civil Aviation Administration of
China, the helicopter had two pilots. One was Japanese, but he was
not identified, the officials said; the other 10 people aboard were
Chinese.
   The officials said the nature of the flight was not known,
although they said it was possible that Asahi Koyo is a company
involved in marine resource development.
   The cause of the crash was not known.
