<FIRST>r a PM-MissingPlane     05-05 0178</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Missing Plane,0182</SECOND>
<HEAD>Missing Plane Found; Pilot and Son Are Dead</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOBART, Okla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Searchers looking for a light plane missing
since Wednesday night found the wreckage near the Wichita Mountains
today and said the pilot and his 5-year-old son were dead.
   ``The Caddo County sheriff has gone in and found two
fatalities,'' said Maj. Barbara Wilson, public affairs officer for
the Oklahoma Wing of the Civil Air Patrol.
   Joe Bickford, 31, of Mountain View, and his son, Jeff, had left
Oklahoma City about 10 p.m. Wednesday bound for Hobart, according
to Paul Gould, assistant manager of Hobart Municipal Airport.
Hobart is about 90 miles southwest of Oklahoma City and 20 miles
west of Mountain View.
   Gould said radar contact with the two-seat plane was lost at
10:15 p.m. near Chickasha, about 60 miles from Hobart.
   The CAP had looked for the plane Thursday but had to call off
the search late in the day because of storms.
   The wreckage was spotted this morning about a mile from the
intersection of Oklahoma Highways 19 and 58.
</TEXT>
