landed, said the report.
   The Pipanema base was headquarters for 1,000 guerrillas, Lusa
said.
   Citing Angolan army sources, the report said 19 rebels died and
about 200 were captured in the attack.
   In Lisbon, a UNITA spokesman said he knew nothing of the attack.
   The rebels have been fighting to force Angola's Marxist
government to share power.
