<FIRST>r a AM-BRF--MIAIdentities     05-05 0170</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--MIA Identities,0173</SECOND>
<HEAD>Four Missing American Servicemen Identified</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HONOLULU (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The remains of four missing American servicemen
returned from Indochina have been identified, the U.S. Navy's
Pacific Command said Friday.
   The remains were among 38 repatriated by Vietnam on Dec. 15,
1988, the Navy said. Fourteen of the 38 remains have been
identified, and attempts to identify the others are continuing, the
statement said.
   The remains of the four servicemen will be flown Tuesday to
Travis Air Force Base in California to be returned to their
families.
   The remains were identified as those of Air Force Lt. Col.
Charles E. Cappelli, of Providence, R.I., who was lost over North
Vietnam on Nov. 17, 1967; Lt. Col. Robert J. Panek, Sr., of
Chicago, who was lost over North Vietnam on Jan. 28, 1970; and
Capt. George B. Lockhart, of Alexandria, Va., who was lost over
North Vietnam on Dec. 21, 1972.
   The identity of the other man is being withheld at the request
of his family, the statement said.
