<FILEID>AP-NR-05-05-89 0803EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>u f BC-Britain-Stocks     05-05 0120</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Britain-Stocks,0127</SECOND>
<HEAD>London Shares Slightly Higher</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices were slightly higher in early trading
today on the London Stock Exchange before release of U.S.
unemployment figures for April.
   At midday, the Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index
was up 2.1 points, or 0.1 percent, at 2,121.1.
   At its best, the index was up 3.4 points shortly after the
opening. It then fell back at mid-morning to show a loss of as much
as 1.7 points.
   The U.S. unemployment report could help determine the near-term
course of the market, which now stands just below its post-crash
best levels, traders said.
   Volume came to 290.7 million shares at midday compared with
321.9 million shares at the same time Thursday.
