<FILEID>AP-NR-05-05-89 2027EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-HBJ     05-05 0120</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-HBJ,0126</SECOND>
<HEAD>Harcourt Brace Jovanovich Loses $116 Million in First Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Harcourt Brace Jovanovich Inc. on Friday
said its loss widened to $116.1 million in the first quarter from a
loss of $35.3 million for the same period a year ago.
   Revenue rose to $315.5 million from $276.7 million a year
earlier.
   Losses increased largely because of rising interest rates on
company debt and higher market costs for new products in the school
publishing division. The losses were offset by better performances
in HBJ's amusement park and insurance businesses, according to the
company's earnings statement.
   Because much of the company's business is seasonal,
first-quarter results aren't necessarily indicative of the entire
year, the company said.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
